'''Tahirikishimarumi no Kami''' (多比理岐志麻流美神, タヒリキシマルミ) is a deity mentioned in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話}}.

== Overview ==
Appearing in the genealogical record of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神}} in the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}}'', Tahirikishimarumi no Kami is described as a fifth-generation descendant of Ōkuninushi. However, the deity's name is mentioned without any associated myths or deeds, leaving its significance and etymology ambiguous. Based on the components "Tahiriki" and "Shimarumi," the name may imply a flat island and sea, but its exact meaning is uncertain.

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (from the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red represents female deities, and yellow represents deities of unknown gender.]]
Tahirikishimarumi no Kami is the child of {{ill|Mikamunohikono Kami|ja|甕主日子神}}, the fourth-generation descendant of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神}}, and {{ill|Hinarashihime|ja|比那良志毘売}}, the daughter of {{ill|Okami no Kami|ja|淤加美神}}. Tahirikishimarumi no Kami marries {{ill|Ikutama Sakutama Hime no Kami|ja|活玉前玉比売神}}, the daughter of {{ill|Hihiragi no Sono Hanamazumi no Kami|ja|ヒヒラギノソノハナマヅミ}}, and has a child, {{ill|Mironami no Kami|ja|美呂浪神}}.

== Shrine ==
